RECOLED: Collaboative editor with extensive text logging audio
recording capabilities  
--------------------------------------------------------------

See:

o Bouamrane, D. King, S. Luz, and M. Masoodian.: A framework for
  collaborative writing with recording and post-meeting retrieval
  capabilities. IEEE Distributed Systems Online, 2004.
  (http://www.cs.tcd.ie/~luzs/publications/BouamraneKingLuzMasoodian04.pdf)

and

o Massodian, M., Luz, S., Bouamrane, M. and King, D.: RECOLED: A
  Group-Aware Collaborative Text Editor for Capturing Document
  History. Proceedings of IADIS/WWW Internet 2005. 
  (http://www.cs.tcd.ie/~luzs/publications/MasoodianLuzEtAlWWW05.pdf)


CONTENTS
--------

This directory contains the recoled source code and some
documentation. 

REQUIREMENTS:
-------------

RECOLED depends on recplaj and on the Java Shared Data Toolkit (jsdt;
version 2.0 or better). The required libraries have been included
with this recoled source distribution. 

If you are a devceloper, see

http://cowrat.berlios.de/recplaj/

and 

https://jsdt.dev.java.net/

for details.


RUNNING RECOLED
---------------

Start the server:

% cd lib ; java -jar recoled-server.jar &

  (or double-click on recoled-server.jar)

Start a client:

% cd lib ; java -jar recoled-server.jar &

  (or double-click on recoled-client.jar)

